The paper deals with submodular functions, which are a fundamental concept in discrete optimization and machine learning. The paper also mentions applications in feature selection, data summarization, movie recommendation, online link prediction, and the design of course sequences for MOOCs. These topics are closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
